    abstract = {Background: Glucose sensors measure glucose concentration in the interstitial fluid ({ISF}), remote from blood. {ISF} glucose is well known to be “delayed” with respect to blood glucose ({BG}). However, {ISF} glucose is not simply a shifted-in-time version of {BG} but exhibits a more complex pattern.
    
